 {"id":"br-97gc6","title":"Repo-wide bug-burn audit and remediation program","description":"# Repo-Wide Bug-Burn Audit and Remediation Program

## Why
Fresh-eyes passes keep surfacing real bugs in unrelated parts of the workspace, which means confidence is currently being overstated by local familiarity and uneven verification. The right response is not more vibes or isolated fixes; it is a repo-wide, multi-pass audit program with explicit intake, subsystem slices, blocker tracking, and convergence criteria.

## Objective
Turn repo-wide bug hunting into a tractable, resumable execution program that:
- slices the workspace by subsystem instead of mixing unrelated surfaces
- uses the same pass structure in every slice: map -> audit -> fix -> rescan -> verify
- records every concrete bug as a bead or linked closure note instead of losing findings in chat
- captures current infrastructure blockers that prevent trustworthy verification
- converges to an explicit residual-risk register rather than an endless stream of ad hoc fixes

## Scope
This program covers core, DB, storage, guard, tools, server, TUI, robot, CLI, share, search, conformance, E2E harnesses, and the backlog/tooling surfaces required to run the audit sanely.

## Acceptance Criteria
- every major subsystem has an explicit audit lane with a repeatable pass checklist
- infra/tooling blockers that distort audit results are tracked explicitly
- newly discovered bugs are linked into the correct subsystem lane with verification evidence
- the audit ends with an explicit residual-risk register, not an implicit "probably fine"","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-18T22:52:33.274853574Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T22:52:33.274853574Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","bug-burn","quality","repo-wide","verification"]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.1","title":"Bug-burn control plane: scope, audit rubric, and intake workflow","description":"Create the control plane for the audit so future work does not depend on chat archaeology.

Deliverables:
