+{"id":"br-97gc6.1.1.1","title":"Inventory: reconcile agent visibility across inbox, robot surfaces, and recent coordination traffic","description":"Record the mismatch between Agent Mail inbox activity and am robot agents output. Determine which surfaces are authoritative for currently active agents, whether robot output is scoped or stale, and how the audit should reference active names without overclaiming.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:41:01.743614444Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T17:51:25.373064130Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","coordination","planning"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.1.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.1.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:41:01.743614444Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1266,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.1.1","author":"TopazIbis","text":"Evidence on 2026-03-19 after recovering the repo-local Agent Mail DB: `am robot agents --active --project /data/projects/mcp_agent_mail_rust` reported only `TopazIbis`, `PlumKnoll`, and `WindyGate` as active. `am robot reservations --project /data/projects/mcp_agent_mail_rust --all` simultaneously showed an active exclusive reservation held by `GrayHeron` on `crates/mcp-agent-mail-db/src/reconstruct.rs`, and `am robot timeline --since 2026-03-19T17:30:00Z` showed `GrayHeron reserved crates/mcp-agent-mail-db/src/reconstruct.rs` at `2026-03-19T17:41:37Z`. Code inspection shows `build_agents()` in `crates/mcp-agent-mail-cli/src/robot.rs` classifies active strictly from `agents.last_active_ts >= now - 15m`, while reservations/timeline come from independent queries over `file_reservations` and `messages`. The reconstructed archive state also appears to create misleading placeholder agents: `PlumKnoll` and `WindyGate` show reconstruct-time `last_active_ts` with `program/model = unknown`, but there are no corresponding archive `agents/<name>/profile.json` files under `/home/ubuntu/.mcp_agent_mail_git_mailbox_repo/projects/data-projects-mcp-agent-mail-rust/agents/`; only `GrayHeron/profile.json` exists among the currently visible names. So the current surfaces are not reporting a single coherent notion of active agents: robot roster is DB-liveness by `last_active_ts`, reservations/timeline reflect actual recent coordination events, and reconstruct-created placeholder agents can look active despite missing agent profiles.","created_at":"2026-03-19T17:51:25Z"}]}
+{"id":"br-97gc6.1.1.2","title":"Inventory: snapshot dirty worktree surfaces and likely ownership boundaries","description":"Capture the current modified file set, note likely owner or active-agent overlap where known, and identify which subsystems are safe for the next audit pass without colliding with in-flight edits.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:41:28.548959426Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T17:51:56.118770902Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","coordination","planning"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.1.2","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.1.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:41:28.548959426Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1267,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.1.2","author":"TopazIbis","text":"Snapshot on 2026-03-19 17:51Z: `git status --short` currently shows only `.beads/issues.jsonl` modified in the worktree. `git diff --stat` agrees: 1 file changed, 4 insertions / 3 deletions, and `git diff -- Cargo.lock crates/mcp-agent-mail-db/src/reconstruct.rs` is currently empty. The remaining live ownership constraint is not a dirty file but an active Agent Mail reservation: `am robot reservations --project /data/projects/mcp_agent_mail_rust --all --format json` shows `GrayHeron` holding an exclusive reservation on `crates/mcp-agent-mail-db/src/reconstruct.rs` for ~49 more minutes. Practical boundary from this snapshot: Beads/coordination files are locally dirty, `crates/mcp-agent-mail-db/src/reconstruct.rs` should be treated as in-flight due to GrayHeron even though it is not currently dirty, and the rest of the repo appears clean/safe for new audit passes from a worktree-conflict perspective.","created_at":"2026-03-19T17:51:56Z"}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.1.2","title":"Control plane: define pass checklist and evidence contract for every subsystem audit","description":"Write the repeatable pass structure for every subsystem lane: 1) map execution/data flow, 2) audit with fresh eyes, 3) fix concrete issues, 4) rerun targeted verification with rch where CPU-heavy, 5) record residual risks/open blockers. Define required evidence fields for each closed audit item.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T22:53:09.013134761Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:49:01.326993619Z","closed_at":"2026-03-18T23:49:01.326363720Z","close_reason":"Completed: subsystem audit checklist and evidence contract are now explicit for all lanes","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","evidence","process"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.2","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T22:53:09.013134761Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.2","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:12:30.149592204Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1263,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.2","author":"ubuntu","text":"Per-subsystem audit contract on 2026-03-18: (1) map the slice first by tracing entry points, imports, and adjacent state transitions; (2) run a fresh-eyes audit looking for concrete correctness issues, confusing semantics, and edge-case failures; (3) fix only confirmed defects and add focused regression coverage where the repo already tests nearby behavior; (4) offload CPU-heavy verification with rch, recording exact commands plus any upstream blockers; (5) record residual risks, non-local blockers, and whether the slice is clean, partially verified, or blocked. Required evidence for a closed audit item: files traced, concrete finding or explicit no-finding statement, tests/verification attempted, blocker provenance if verification is incomplete, and any follow-up beads spawned.","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:48:52Z"}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.1.3","title":"Control plane: define bug intake, closure, and reopen rules for discovered defects","description":"Specify when a found defect gets its own bug bead, when it can be closed as part of a parent audit bead, what verification proof is required, and when a previously closed item must be reopened after a regression or conflicting evidence.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T22:53:20.626743612Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:12:41.637239747Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","process","tracking"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.3","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T22:53:20.626743612Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.3","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:12:41.635658627Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.1.4","title":"Control plane: reconcile bug-burn scope with br-aazao and active ATC epics","description":"Map overlap between this bug-burn program, the existing verification epic br-aazao, and active ATC epics such as br-0qt6e*. Output should say what is reused, what is complementary, and what should not be duplicated.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T22:53:20.810353305Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:48:34.200276696Z","closed_at":"2026-03-18T23:48:34.199638943Z","close_reason":"Completed: scope split between bug-burn, verification-realism, and ATC implementation epics is now explicit","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","coordination","planning"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.4","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T22:53:20.810353305Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1262,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.1.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Scope reconciliation on 2026-03-18: br-97gc6 is the repo-wide bug-burn program for defect discovery, remediation, and residual-risk tracking across subsystems. br-aazao is the complementary verification-realism program for unit/integration/E2E coverage claims, sanctioned substitutes, and logging/artifact quality. br-0qt6e* remains the ATC learning implementation/design program. Reuse rules: if the audit finds a concrete code defect, track/fix it under br-97gc6 or the relevant subsystem/feature bead; if it finds a coverage or test-realism gap without a code correctness defect, route it to br-aazao; if it exposes missing ATC capability/design work rather than a regression, route it to br-0qt6e*. Avoid duplicating the same obligation across all three epics.","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:48:25Z"}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.2","title":"Bug-burn support: tracker stabilization, dependency wiring, and audit bookkeeping","description":"Stabilize the operational scaffolding around the bug-burn program itself: diagnose slow/hang-like br writes, keep the bead graph coherent, add missing dependencies as the audit evolves, and ensure the tracker/export state stays trustworthy while the repo-wide audit is in flight.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T22:57:51.691401925Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:12:07.443311668Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","blockers","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.2","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T22:57:51.691401925Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.2.1","title":"Tracker stabilization: reproduce mutations that persist successfully but still return DATABASE_ERROR busy","description":"At least one br close mutation on 2026-03-18 returned a database-is-busy error to the caller even though the issue state persisted as closed. Reproduce that false-negative client outcome, determine whether it is a lock-timeout/reporting bug, and record a safe workaround for the remainder of the audit.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:47:20.929782585Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:47:20.929782585Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","blockers","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.2.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:47:20.929782585Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.3","title":"Bug-burn blockers: backlog integrity, tooling health, and verification blockers","description":"Track the tooling and graph problems that can distort audit output or waste effort. Deliverables: explicit blocker ledger for br, bv, rch, compile/test, and local repo health anomalies; triage which blockers must be fixed first versus merely worked around; dependencies from subsystem lanes onto blockers only when truly necessary.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:04:45.442741681Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:04:45.442741681Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","blockers","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:04:45.442741681Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"br-97gc6.3.1","title":"Blockers: diagnose br doctor WAL/SHM anomaly and preserved recovery artifacts","description":"Investigate the current br doctor warnings about preserved recovery artifacts and a WAL sidecar without matching SHM. Determine whether this is stale debris, a real consistency risk, or a benign leftover; record a safe remediation path without destructive cleanup.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:06:42.249742525Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:48.131086289Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["beads","db","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:06:42.249742525Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1260,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Evidence on 2026-03-18: the live anomaly is specific to .beads/beads.db-wal existing without .beads/beads.db-shm. After the long-running br writer exited, lsof showed no remaining open handles on beads.db or beads.db-wal, but the WAL file still persisted. Preserved recovery artifacts are separate from that live complaint: .beads/.br_recovery contains beads.db.20260313_224031_514673114.bak and beads.db-wal.orphan_20260313T224229Z, while the repo root also contains historical beads.db.bad_*, beads.db.rebuild_*, vacuum/reindex test files, and recovery_20260313T224002Z.","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:48Z"}]}
+{"id":"br-97gc6.3.1","title":"Blockers: diagnose br doctor WAL/SHM anomaly and preserved recovery artifacts","description":"Investigate the current br doctor warnings about preserved recovery artifacts and a WAL sidecar without matching SHM. Determine whether this is stale debris, a real consistency risk, or a benign leftover; record a safe remediation path without destructive cleanup.","status":"in_progress","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:06:42.249742525Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T17:47:01.512425476Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["beads","db","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:06:42.249742525Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1260,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Evidence on 2026-03-18: the live anomaly is specific to .beads/beads.db-wal existing without .beads/beads.db-shm. After the long-running br writer exited, lsof showed no remaining open handles on beads.db or beads.db-wal, but the WAL file still persisted. Preserved recovery artifacts are separate from that live complaint: .beads/.br_recovery contains beads.db.20260313_224031_514673114.bak and beads.db-wal.orphan_20260313T224229Z, while the repo root also contains historical beads.db.bad_*, beads.db.rebuild_*, vacuum/reindex test files, and recovery_20260313T224002Z.","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:48Z"},{"id":1265,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"TopazIbis","text":"Evidence on 2026-03-19: `am macros start-session` initially failed in `/data/projects/mcp_agent_mail_rust` because repo-local `./storage.sqlite3` was malformed and had a stale `storage.sqlite3-wal` sidecar without a live repo-local holder. `lsof storage.sqlite3 storage.sqlite3-wal` in the repo showed no open handles. The unhealthy listener on port 8765 is a separate process (`/home/ubuntu/.local/bin/am`, pid 3943291, cwd `/home/ubuntu`) holding `/home/ubuntu/storage.sqlite3` and `/home/ubuntu/storage.sqlite3-wal`, so it is not the writer for the repo-local DB. Safe non-destructive remediation for the repo-local mailbox DB was: 1) verify no repo-local open handles, 2) run `AM_INTERFACE_MODE=cli am doctor reconstruct --dry-run --json`, 3) run `AM_INTERFACE_MODE=cli am doctor reconstruct --yes --json`. That quarantined the corrupt DB to `storage.sqlite3.corrupt-*` artifacts and rebuilt a fresh `./storage.sqlite3` from the Git mailbox archive, after which `am doctor check` reported the DB accessible and I could register as `TopazIbis`. Residual findings after reconstruct: archive/db parity still fails (`messages archive=1951 db=1292`), `schema_version` is `user_version = 0`, the archive contains duplicate canonical message ids and missing `project.json` files for some archived projects, and the repo now has preserved `storage.sqlite3*.corrupt-*` / salvage artifacts by design rather than active live-state debris. Separate but related tracker evidence: `.beads/beads.db-wal` still exists without `.beads/beads.db-shm`, `br doctor` still reports that anomaly, and `br update` for this bead persisted the status change to `in_progress` but returned `UNIQUE constraint failed: blocked_issues_cache.issue_id`, so Beads mutation reporting needs separate follow-up.","created_at":"2026-03-19T17:47:01Z"}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.3.1.1","title":"Tracker blocker: classify live beads DB sidecars versus preserved recovery artifacts","description":"Distinguish the currently relevant live database state from preserved historical rebuild or orphan artifacts under .beads. The output should identify which files are evidence, which are stale debris, and which ones br doctor is actually complaining about today.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:41:45.312405542Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:53.880724262Z","closed_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:53.880032217Z","close_reason":"Completed: distinguished the live beads.db WAL-sidecar anomaly from preserved historical recovery artifacts","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","blockers","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:41:45.312405542Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.3.1.2","title":"Tracker blocker: define safe non-destructive remediation path for stale beads recovery debris","description":"After the artifact classification is done, document a safe remediation policy that does not require deleting anything during the audit. Include what can be ignored, what should be quarantined later with explicit approval, and what would justify escalation.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:42:00.171611958Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:47:04.888550523Z","closed_at":"2026-03-18T23:47:04.887932135Z","close_reason":"Completed: documented safe non-destructive remediation policy for the tracker anomaly during the audit","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","blockers","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:42:00.171611958Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1261,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1.2","author":"ubuntu","text":"Safe remediation policy for the current audit: do not delete any .beads artifacts manually; treat the WAL-without-SHM condition as non-blocking only while sqlite integrity, DB-vs-JSONL counts, and br doctor write_probe remain green; serialize br mutations to one writer at a time; if the anomaly worsens or counts diverge, stop tracker writes, preserve the current .beads state, and use br doctor --repair during a quiet window instead of ad hoc cleanup. Historical .bad/.rebuild/.br_recovery files require explicit human approval before any deletion or archival action.","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:46:56Z"}]}
